This paper is primarily focused on sentiment analysis, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also extensively uses neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for sentiment analysis, which falls under the category of computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper uses gated architectures, which is a relatively new concept in neural networks and falls under the category of neural engineering (NE). Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely sub-category.
